<main class="container my-5" aria-labelledby="title">
    <h1 id="title" class="mb-4">About the Project</h1>

    <div class="mb-5">
        <p class="lead">
            The Optimization & Scheduling System is a web-based application built on ASP.NET MVC designed
            to optimize driver shift scheduling with advanced algorithms, balancing driver preferences,
            performance, and operational requirements.
        </p>
    </div>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <h2 class="mb-3">Project Overview</h2>
        <p>
            This system integrates the Gurobi optimization engine to automate complex scheduling problems,
            enabling drivers and managers to interact with the scheduling process seamlessly.
            It offers role-based access, persistent data storage with PostgreSQL, and a modular architecture.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <h2 class="mb-3">Key Features</h2>
        <ul class="feature-list list-unstyled ps-3">
            <li>Driver Scheduling Optimization using integer programming models.</li>
            <li>Preference-Based Assignment allowing drivers to select preferred routes and shifts.</li>
            <li>Performance-Aware Scheduling prioritizing high-performing drivers.</li>
            <li>Backup Assignments for coverage in emergencies or no-shows.</li>
            <li>Role-Based Access Control securing manager-only features.</li>
            <li>Persistent storage of scheduling results in PostgreSQL.</li>
            <li>Clean, modular architecture for maintainability and extensibility.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

